New Features

Mobile push notifications

- End-to-end mobile push: iOS APNs token registration and Android FCM
- Rich-media notifications via the Notification Service Extension (ConnectNSE) and Notification Content Extension (ConnectNCE), rendering expanded content

Expo support (SDK 55+)

- Bundled Expo Config Plugin: provisions the ConnectNSE + ConnectNCE Xcode targets during `expo prebuild` (idempotent across re-runs, generated from the bundled NotificationViewController.swift template), adds the host-app `aps-environment` entitlement, and propagates `ConnectConfig.json` into the Android build — so APNs and FCM push work in Expo apps
- EAS Build support for the NSE + NCE extension targets, with a sample `eas.json` in `Examples/expo`
- Expo SDK 55+ sample app (`Examples/expo`) on expo-router, sharing the push/identity UI with the bare-workflow sample via `Examples/shared`

Bug Fixes

- Fix invalid AppKey shadowing: consumer's ConnectConfig.json AppKey now overrides the Connect AAR's baked-in default on Android
- Fix iOS runtime crash "Library not loaded: @rpath/EOCore.framework/EOCore" on newer merged Acoustic Connect SDK variants
- Fix Connect component breaking host-app touch handling when wrapped NavigationContainer has no ref
- Fix React 19 compatibility and constrain nitro-modules peer dep
- Fix ConnectConfig.json template
- Fix version update script for Android
- Expo: pass the dev-client URI scheme to `expo start` so the QR / deep link connects when the push NSE/NCE extensions are present
- bare-workflow: drop the CocoaPods git Specs source from the Podfile so a cold `pod install` no longer syncs the multi-GB Specs repo

Improvements:

- New explicit `navigationRef` prop on <Connect> for ref passing without relying on children structure
- Rebuild SDK using nitro-modules 0.35.9
- Android: resolve react-native version conflicts from transitive Gradle deps
- iOS: verbose Connect/Tealeaf/EOCore native logging when `useRelease:false`, surfaced in the Xcode console for QA and support
- CI: Expo iOS + Android sample-build gates

Our environment for this release:

- Xcode 26.2
- MacOS 26.0.1
- iOS 15.1 to 26.x
- Supported architectures:
	- simulator
		- arm64
		- x86_64
	- device
		- arm64


Known Issues

- After iOS 13, library no longer supports iPad because of Apple changes in iPad OS.
- Dual sim features are in beta. Example information using multiple carriers.
